Melt butter in an electric pressure cooker on the "Saute" setting. Add garlic; cook and stir until fragrant, about 2 minutes. Add cauliflower and chicken stock. Seal cooker and bring to high pressure according to manufacturer's directions. Cook for 6 minutes. Release pressure naturally according to manufacturer's instructions. Remove the lid carefully. Blend cauliflower with an immersion blender until creamy. Thin with water to desired consistency; stir in Parmesan cheese. Season with salt and pepper.